HEADWORD: Drumlin
<hw>Drum"lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gael.
<ets>druim</ets> the ridge of a hill.]</ety> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A
hill of compact, unstratified, glacial drift or till, usually elongate
or oval, with the larger axis parallel to the former local glacial
motion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

